text: This development is fascinating as well as it scares me.. Scientists have just combined a biological cell from a frog with artificial manmade technology. It grows together as one cell, that is able to fix itself. It acts totally independent. It is theoretically possible to create cyborgs with this very new technology.. it's supposed to clean human arteries for example, fix diseases and even cure paralysis...the possibilities are theoretically entire...but still, we should not overrate the machines. They clearly have their limits and we should maybe think about what we let into our lifes by giving computers so much power over us...we already depend on computers. A whole city gets hacked and nothing works anymore ( it happened in a little city, somehere in Germany..and the Bundestag, headquarters of the German government had been hacked too..many private documents were stolen )..An other example for it's limits we should maybe except: Human creativity.An AI studied Beethoven's way of composing for two years. They then had a computer complete Beethoven's 10th symphony based on endlessly collected algorithms, which he was unable to complete because he died beforehand. The result was clear. An AI is not able to work out increases emotions with music like a human. The music had no soul.
